du -ah --block-size=1G --max-depth=1 | sort -rh
To handle this situation, you can modify the command slightly to limit 
the depth of the directory traversal. For example, you can specify 
a specific directory or limit the depth using the --max-depth option. Here's an example:

**du -ah --block-size=1G --max-depth=1 | sort -rh**

In this command, --max-depth=1 limits the depth of the directory traversal to 1 level.
You can adjust the value as per your requirement.
This modified command will list the files in the specified directory (or the current directory if no directory is specified), 
sorted from the biggest size to the smallest size, with the sizes displayed in GB.
